cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper proposes a decentralised MARL algorithm enhanced by a prediction mechanism that provides accurate information regarding up-coming changes in the environment. This involves the use of Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs) and Self-Organising Maps (SOMs) to detect and match changes in the environment. This falls under the domain of AI. 
2. cs.LG - The paper proposes a learning algorithm that uses reinforcement learning to optimize control in a decentralised system. This falls under the domain of machine learning. 
3. cs.MA - The paper proposes a multi-agent system that uses reinforcement learning to optimize control in a decentralised system. This falls under the domain of multi-agent systems. 
4. cs.SY - The paper proposes a system that deals with dynamic and uncertain environments, which is a characteristic of complex systems. This falls under the domain of systems engineering. 
5. cs.NE - The paper proposes the use of Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs) to detect and match changes in the environment. This falls under the domain of neural networks.
